why do wolfs hawl at the moon wolves are social animals howling is a kind of 'singing' that has a communal purpose and declares the wolf's territory they howl to keep contact with other wolves and are able to discriminate pack members from rivals their howling can cover great distances they usually howl during twilight hours whether the moon is visible or not and they howl more often during breeding season and the subsequent rearing process they also howl when they are nervous i think it is simply coincidental that some of their howling occurs on moonlit nights Gray Wolf Coyote Wolf's Rain Domestication Pack (canine) The Howling Tai shogi The Howling Man Therianthropy Taikyoku shogi Dog Howl The Twilight Zone USS Tunny (SS-282) Howlin' Wolf Second Battle of the Atlantic Housebreaking Dai dai shogi Wolfman Jack USS Atule (SS-403) Extraterrestrial skies Moon Thunderbolts (comics) Galaxy Angel Valkyrie The Wolf Man Eclipse Fritz Leiber Beat generation Asteroid Mercury (planet) Parallax Astronomy on Mars Tide Castlevania: Symphony of the Night Otherkin Alaskan Malamute Animal communication Howl's Moving Castle Werewolf: The Apocalypse Solar eclipse Tasmanian Devil Capercaillie Jupiter Venus Fafhrd and the Gray Mouser Livestock Naval mine Fox Fermi paradox Greatest (Duran Duran) Buzz or Howl Under the Influence of Heat Apollo moon landing hoax accusations Fox hunting Dingo Clementine mission Hebrew calendar Caravan of Courage: An Ewok Adventure Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Starfleet ranks and insignia Films that have been considered the greatest ever Keith Moon Satchel Paige Elves (Elfquest) Gregorian calendar Gerrymandering Outlaw Star Symbionese Liberation Army Wolf interval Baseball History of Vilnius State The Dream-Quest of Unknown Kadath Fenrisulfr Crispin Freeman Yellowstone National Park South Park The Descent of Man, and Selection in Relation to Sex Steampunk TV-FM DX Comet Shoemaker-Levy 9 Calendar Endometrium Berserker Pink Floyd trivia Bosniaks Omaha Race Riot of